Statute.definition: a law enacted by the legislative branch of a government see also code
Statute.origin: [Latin statutum law, regulation, from neuter of statutus , past participle of statuere to set up, station, from status position, state]

1.definition: a law enacted by the legislative branch of a government see also,

2.definition: an act of a corporation or its founder intended as a permanent rule

3.definition: an international instrument setting up an agency and regulating its scope or authority [the of the International Court of Justice]
